Salinity and conductivity were measured with a conductivity meter (DDSJ-308F, Leici, China). Organic acids were measured using a high-performance liquid chromatography apparatus (1260, Agilent Technologies, USA) (Nevin et al. 2010). Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) was performed through a potentiostat (CHI660D, Shanghai Chen Hua Instrument Co., Ltd., China). The cathode, anode, and Ag/AgCl were used as working electrode, counter electrode, and reference electrodes, respectively. The frequency range of the EIS was 0.01–100 kHz. The Coulombic efficiency (CE) was calculated as CE=CP/CT×100%,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
